## TailwindCSS + daisyUI Rules

- Use daisyUI component classes first: `btn`, `card`, `chat`, `alert`, `badge`, `modal`
- Use Tailwind utilities for spacing and sizing only when daisyUI doesn't cover it
- Do not write raw CSS unless a daisyUI/Tailwind combination genuinely can't achieve it
- Do not inline `style={{}}` props — use className
- Theme switching: use `data-theme` attribute on `<html>`. Provide light + dark themes.

```tsx
// Good — daisyUI semantic classes
<button className="btn btn-primary btn-sm">Send</button>
<div className="alert alert-error" role="alert">Error message</div>
<span className="badge badge-warning">fallback</span>

// Bad — raw Tailwind colors instead of semantic tokens
<button className="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Send</button>
```

