## TypeScript Rules

- Strict mode: `"strict": true` in tsconfig — no exceptions
- No `any` — use `unknown` at external API boundaries, then narrow with type guards
- All API response types defined in `src/types/api.ts`
- All SSE event types defined in `src/hooks/useSSE.ts`
- Prefer `interface` for object shapes, `type` for unions and computed types

```typescript
// Correct: unknown at boundary, guard for narrowing
function isSSEEvent(data: unknown): data is SSEEvent {
  return typeof data === "object" && data !== null && "type" in data
}

// Wrong: any silences the type system
function handleEvent(data: any) { ... }
```

